		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />You know, I could have easily gone down the path of using lots of hot melt glue in my electronic projects. That the stuff turns into spider webs and gets caught up in everything is probably the biggest reason I avoid it most of the time. I can't stand those little strings stretching out. I think the high-temperature glue sticks might be better, but it's not common or cheap.

		

		</td>
